<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1699" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1699">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 881.00/608.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Ambassador <persName type="to">Sharp</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 793.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 29, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department herewith encloses to you a
                            copy of a despatch dated December 8, No. 506, from the American Chargé
                            at Tangier, relative to the decision of the French Resident General in
                            Morocco that certain cases hitherto tried before the civil courts shall
                            be tried before the French military courts, even in cases where the
                            persons concerned are citizens of a capitulatory country.</p>
                        <p>In order to prevent any waiver by the United States of its rights in
                            Morocco, you will call the attention of the French Government to this
                            action of the French Resident General in Morocco and protest against it
                            in so far as it affects citizens of the United States.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank L. Polk.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>